main event: On January 3, 1966, two witnesses observed a solid white, cigar-shaped object moving in a straight and level course over Burbank, Ohio for about 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was visible for about 5 minutes and was described as bright white and cigar-shaped,The witnesses estimated the object's speed at 520 mph and its distance at about 5 miles,The object gradually disappeared while remaining bright in the sky,The sky conditions were believed to be cloudy during the observation,One of the witnesses was a male, 45 years old, who had drafting experience.
witness description: One witness was a 45-year-old male with a background in drafting.
